Track Nutanix alerts through their full lifecycle with per-state metrics (`nutanix.alert.open`, `nutanix.alert.acknowledged`, `nutanix.alert.resolved`), state-transition events (acknowledged, reopened, resolved), and a default monitor template. Each metric carries `ext_id` for per-alert monitor grouping, plus Tier-1 tags (`ntnx_originating_cluster_name`, `ntnx_alert_user_defined`, `ntnx_alert_service`). Alert collection is reconciled against the v4.0 unresolved-alerts API every cycle (`$filter=isResolved eq false`) so missed resolutions can no longer leave orphaned metrics.